        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 5:47PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 6 miles northeast of McNeil to 5 miles
southeast of Junction City, moving southwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Magnolia, Waldo, Junction City, McNeil, Haynesville, Bernice,
Emerson, Atlanta, Wesson, Village, Mount Holly, Cooley, Calhoun,
Spearsville, Lillie, Hew Hope, Three Creeks, Marysville and
Spotville.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
